Firstly, what I am most opposed to, when I mention the bit about pet commands, is that Verant just say learn how to controll your pet. They don't take into account things that may make this hard at times. Things like lag. And lag does not only affect pet handlers, also enchanters and bard, to mention two, are greatly affected by it.<P>I consider myself a pretty good pet handler, but everyone, even the best ones, can have their pet start beating on mobs they should not. And it will kill the group at times, pissing a lot of people off. I think that a command that would stop your pet from changing target mid fight would be a good help. Then again, I may just be a "useless stupid mage whining for pet commands". It is not a big issue, what I wanted most was all group spells / songs to include pets. As for some of the things you mention, like the epic.. if you read the post by Verant, you will see that epic quests are NOT a part of the issue here, they are covered elsewhere. I just want to stop my pet from attacking something that may hit me mid fight.. if I tell my pet to attack something, I want it to stay on that mob until I call it off. Not start beating on something else. <P>And it may only be me, but someone who has played a mage to level 55 should know at least a little bit about how to play his or her class, no ? ... play a mage like a tank, shees. I don't know how other play, but I play my mage as a mage /shrug<P>Ps, I never wanted DoT's in the first place, so..<P>Mordread Draconius<BR>Conjurer<BR>Rodcet Nife
