As far as I can tell, the only real issue with the class is damage output at post 50 levels<P>It takes a lot of skill and work to get your pet working at it's best and not ****ing the group up in a dangerous area... but when you do so, you and your pet should be able to outdamage anyone else in the game.  That's our primary role, and we have to work hardest to do it effectively in dangerous areas... risk vs reward.  If we're getting outdamaged by rogues and monks, and barely beating warriors... what's the point?<P>The class is broken when this happens, and VI refuses to see that.<P>The problem isn't class abilities though, it's class equipment.  On a new server, mages rock... our damage output is awesome.. as the server gets older and people get higher levels... more nice weapons flow into the market... the gap decreases...<P>on old servers now at the upper levels, all the melee classes have uber equipment that boosts their damage output up over ours... there is no equipment that adds effectiveness to a mage, except for our focus items, and those have been around forever.  And they don't affect our pets as much as uber equipment helps a melee.  Every day I see more and more uber items coming into the game.. just the other day I saw a rogue weapon that does better regular melee damage than a ragebringer, but wut had 1 point less damage... overall it'd be about equal probably, as far as pure damage output goes.  Same goes for every melee class.  They're getting more and more uber and VI thinks that we're balanced because with self-obtained items we probably would be... but the fact is, there are so mnay nice weapons out there, our damage output lags behind.  We have one thing that we can do well... one thing and ONLY one thing... applying damage to the mobs... we should be able to do that better than anyone else.  We don't.  The class is broken post 50.
